source_intake_record.raw_question_text:
Two particles (masses $m_1$ and $m_2$) are attached to the ends of a massless rigid rod of length $a$. The system is free to rotate in three dimensions about the (fixed) center of mass.Figure shows a portion of the rotational spectrum of carbon monoxide (CO). What is the frequency separation } (\Delta 
u) \text{ between adjacent lines? Look up the masses of }^{12}\text{C and }^{16}\text{O, and from } m_1, m_2, \text{ and } \Delta 
u \text{ determine the distance between the atoms.}

